  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Additional security support for expansion of the humanitarian operations in specific area in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Humanitarian Country Team is addressing the humanitarian situation in Yemen, especially in the Southern and Northern Governorates. One of the components to enable the implementation of the  operation is security support and coordination, which will enable humanitarian missions to be conducted in a safe and secure manner especially in very high security risk areas.

The objective of the project is to provide dedicated safety security support as facilities assessment, road movements advisories, manual security clearance, organizing and enable security escorts, issuance of security advisories rather than movements, mission tracking, general/particular security assessment for specific areas, advise on personnel ceiling and/or curfew hours, liaison with national authorities in order to facilitate the expanded lifesaving humanitarian operations to create safety and security conditions and to deploy the necessary UN suppor,t enabling effective delivery of humanitarian assistance in the affected regions.</narrative>
  </description>
